title: Season ends for Blackhawk netters
text:
Season ends for Blackhawk netters 
STOUGHTON — Upset hopes fell short for the Fort Atkinson girls tennis team at the WIAA Division 1 girls’ tennis Subsectional at Stoughton on Tuesday. 
The Blackhawks didn’t have anyone advance into sectionals and weren’t able to score a team point on the day. 
At No. 1 singles Emma Hartwig fell to an advancing Dao Sysouvahn of Sun Prairie, 6-0, 6-0. Mackenzie Chady lost 6-1, 6-1 to Milton’s Ashley Lester in No. 2. 
At No. 3 Ari Wheeler fell to Milton’s Kylie Robinson and at No 4. Stephany Sykes fell 6-0, 6-0 to an advancing Katie Tews of Sun Prairie at No. 4. 
Seniors Evalise Yang and Megan Jordan couldn’t play the role of underdog in the No. 1 doubles, falling 6-1, 6-3 to an advancing Faith Dittman and Bethany Crandall from Milton. 
Sarina and Brianna Halvorsen also fell to an advancing team in Holly Brickson and Sydney Johnson. The Stoughton duo beat the Fort seniors 6-0, 6-0. 
In No. 3 doubles Kastyn Hebbe and Hannah Beckman struggled to continue their end of the season form, falling to Watertown’s advancing Gabby Linskens and Calley Wesemann 6-1, 6-0. 
Qualifiers advance to the WIAA Division 1 Stoughton Sectional, which began this morning and will be held throughout the day.
